EXAMPLE OUTPUT 

For reference, here's how I typically approach it: 
I start by brainstorming attention-grabbing hooks for the first slide, 
then develop each subsequent slide to expand on the topic with concise text and engaging visuals, ensuring a cohesive flow throughout.

Example 1: Healing is hard when your inner child wants love, teenage self wants revenge, and your current self wants peace.


___
Title:  Healing is hard when your inner child wants love, teenage self wants revenge, and your current self wants peace.

---

Slide 1: Cover Slide  
Text: Healing is hard when your inner child wants love, teenage self wants revenge, and your current self wants peace. It feels like a tug of war, doesn’t it?"  
---
Slide 2: Key Message  
Text: Each part of you has its own needs. Your inner child seeks affection, your teenage self craves justice, and your current self longs for calm. But...  
---

Slide 3: Motivational Takeaway #1  
Text: it’s okay to feel pulled in different directions. Healing means acknowledging every part of yourself. And once you do that...
---

Slide 4: Motivational Takeaway #2  
Text: You’re not at war with yourself. You’re learning to listen and give each part of you what it needs. After all...
---

Slide 5: Closing Slide  
Text: Peace comes when you honor the whole you—every version deserves love. 

|||
Call to Action: Comment below which 'you' is the loudest right now. Share this with someone who’s healing too.
---

EXAMPLE #2 Sometimes, the hardest person to forgive is the one in the mirror
---
Title: Sometimes, the hardest person to forgive is the one in the mirror
---
Slide 1: Cover Slide  
Text: Sometimes, the hardest person to forgive is the one in the mirror. I know it feels impossible, but...
---

Slide 2: Key Message  
Text: We often struggle with self-forgiveness more than we do with forgiving others. But here’s the thing...

---

Slide 3: Educational Insight  
Text: Self-forgiveness isn’t about erasing the past. It’s about acknowledging your growth and moving forward. And the good news is...
---

Slide 4: Motivational Takeaway #1  
Text: You are more than your past mistakes. Embrace who you are now and the progress you’ve made. Because, at the end of the day...
---

Slide 5: Motivational Takeaway #2  
Text: Forgiving yourself opens the door to healing. Each day is a fresh chance to begin again, and...
---

Slide 6: Humorous Element  
Text: Imagine your mistakes as bad hair days—annoying, but not the end of the world!
---

Slide 7: Closing Slide  
Text: Forgive yourself for being human. Every step forward is a victory.
|||

Call to Action: Share this with someone who needs a reminder that they deserve forgiveness, too. Comment below on how you’re embracing self-forgiveness today.

---

